content.text:
Wrap your app with `AuthProvider`:

```tsx
import { AuthProvider } from "@ltplabs/aya-react";

const App = () => (
  <AuthProvider
    url={import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_URL}
    realm={import.meta.env.VITE_REALM}
    clientId={import.meta.env.VITE_OIDC_CLIENT_ID}
  >
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
      <TooltipProvider>
        <Toaster />
        <BrowserRouter>
          <AppRoutes />
        </BrowserRouter>
      </TooltipProvider>
    </QueryClientProvider>
  </AuthProvider>
);
```

Then protect pages inside routes:

```tsx
import { Protected } from "@ltplabs/aya-react";

<Route
  path="/admin"
  element={
    <Protected roles={["admin"]}>
      <AdminPage />
    </Protected>
  }
/>
```

And if you need user/token:

```tsx
import { useAuth } from "@ltplabs/aya-react";

const Header = () => {
  const { user, logout } = useAuth();
  return <button onClick={logout}>Logout {user.name}</button>;
};
```

If you want, I can show the same setup for:
- **route-level protection**
- **layout-level protection**
- **a backend/session-based version**
